column17: Did not seem to get Likert right away, but got into it. Said didn't remember any noises in any room. Fidgety.
3 y/o "got" game more than 5 y/o. Sometimes pointed or told me colors. Thier room was yellow--did it have an impact?
Mom suggusted practice round b/c she thought child got a lot of info thrown at them at once.
Think they also tried to match face during the first slide.
Used words but also colors of faces.
Judged based on music/if they liked the noise
Odd noise started w/ particpants background at this point
Seemed to choose more on if he liked the tasks versus the sound of the room
Made an acuarate impression of the noise -- did not expressly ID it as talking
Made impression of the noise -- did not expressly ID it as music
*Marked rationale as 1 but child used a library for reasoning so unsure if it should be a different reasoning
*Camera died a minute and ahalf into recording, no data to input
